.SH NAME
brew\-generate\-tap\-completions \- Generate shell completions and man pages for a tap\'s commands
.SH "SYNOPSIS"
\fBbrew\fP \fBgenerate\-tap\-completions\fP [\fB\-\-tap=\fP\fItap\fP] [\fB\-\-no\-exit\-code\fP]
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Generate shell completions and man pages for a tap\[u2019]s commands\.
.P
Reads each \fB*\.rb\fP file in \fBcmd/\fP and writes Bash, ZSH, and Fish completion files into \fBcompletions/\fP, and Ronn man page sources into \fBmanpages/\fP\&\. The tap is auto\-detected from the location of this command file\. Use \fB\-\-tap\fP to override\. Compile man page sources to roff with \fBscripts/generate\-man\-pages\.sh\fP\&\.
.SH "OPTIONS"
.TP
\fB\-d\fP, \fB\-\-debug\fP
Display any debugging information\.
.TP
\fB\-q\fP, \fB\-\-quiet\fP
Make some output more quiet\.
.TP
\fB\-v\fP, \fB\-\-verbose\fP
Make some output more verbose\.
.TP
\fB\-h\fP, \fB\-\-help\fP
Show this message\.
.TP
\fB\-\-tap\fP
Generate completions for \fItap\fP (default: auto\-detected from command location)\.
.TP
\fB\-\-no\-exit\-code\fP
Exit with code 0 even if no changes were made\.
